╭─ Assistant [MainThread@3760636] ─────────────────────────────╮
│ I have analyzed the bug report, the backtrace, and the       │
│ provided root cause analysis. The crash is indeed caused by  │
│ an incorrectly constructed SLP `TreeEntry` for a horizontal  │
│ reduction, which leads to an out-of-bounds access when       │
│ calculating the vectorization cost.                          │
│                                                              │
│ The root cause analysis correctly identifies that when       │
│ building the SLP tree for an instruction within a reduction  │
│ chain, its operand that is also part of the chain is         │
│ mistakenly ignored. This results in a `TreeEntry` with fewer │
│ operands than the instruction it represents, causing the     │
│ assertion failure.                                           │
│                                                              │
│ The fix is to ensure that when `BoUpSLP::buildTree` is       │
│ called for a set of reduction instructions (`VL`), those     │
│ instructions themselves are not present in the ignore list.  │
│ This prevents them from being treated as internal nodes and  │
│ ensures their operands are correctly processed.              │
│                                                              │
│ I will apply this fix by creating a local copy of the        │
│ `IgnoreList` and removing the values in `VL` from it before  │
│ calling `V.buildTree`.                                       │
